-- Kan's Cabinet Approval Rating Drops 18 Points to 50%, Nikkei Survey Shows
-- Lily Nonomiya
-- 2010-06-25T23:54:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/kan-s-cabinet-approval-rating-drops-18-points-to-50-nikkei-survey-shows.html

          
          
             Prime Minister Naoto Kan’s approval
rating fell to 50 percent, 18 percentage points lower than a
poll taken after he was inaugurated, the Nikkei newspaper
reported, citing its own poll.        
 Support for Kan’s ruling Democratic Party of Japan fell 5
percentage points to 42 percent, while approval for the Liberal
Democratic Party rose 3 percentage points to 23 percent,
according to the Nikkei.  
 The survey of 51,381 people was taken June 24 and June 25.
Some 59.2 percent of the responses were valid and the newspaper
did not provide a margin of error.  
